### Test Error CSV Download Feature
### This file demonstrates the error CSV download functionality

### 1. Login as Admin/Teacher
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "teacher@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Store the token from response
@authToken = {{login.response.body.token}}

### 2. Upload CSV with some invalid rows (will generate errors)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/upload/v2/process
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="uploadType"

students
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="students-with-errors.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

Sem,Br,FacultyN,EnrolN,Name,Semester,Hall,SPI,CPI,CumEC,Result
S2221,CE,18CE001,GK1001,John Doe,4,Hall A,8.5,8.2,60,Pass
S2221,,18CE002,GK1002,Jane Smith,4,Hall B,9.0,8.8,60,Pass
S2221,CE,,GK1003,Bob Wilson,0,Hall C,7.5,7.8,55,Pass
S2221,CE,18CE004,,Alice Brown,4,Hall D,8.0,8.5,58,Pass
S2221,CE,18CE005,GK1005,Charlie Davis,4,Hall E,9.5,9.2,62,Pass
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

### Expected Response:
# {
